        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <figure id="f9512021" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9512021.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the old air intake duct from the vehicle. If it's equipped with a snow valve,
                    remove the cable from the snow valve lever before removing the air duct.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drill out the rivets that secure the plastic ring to the air cleaner housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Take care not to damage the air cleaner while removing
                    the ring. Remove anything that may have fallen into the air cleaner housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the tinnerman nut under the ring on the air cleaner, in the rivet hole, at the 12
                    o'clock position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the top of the radiator to see if there is an air duct support bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>). If there is not, mount the bracket as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    with two &#188;"-20 &#215; &#190;" bolts, two flat washers and lock washers. Tighten the bolts to
                    110-140 in-lbs. (12-16 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Transfer the drain valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>) from the old air intake duct to the new air intake
                    duct.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the large end of the air intake duct under the tabs on the air intake duct support
                    bracket on top of the radiator as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512021">Figure 1</hotlnk>, and secure the other end to the ring on the air cleaner
                    with a &#188;"-20 &#215; 1" screw into the tinnerman nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the air intake duct is equipped with a snow valve, fasten the cable to the snow valve
                    lever on the air duct.
                </para>
            </step1>
